==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exhilarate
<hw>Ex*hil"a*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Exhilarated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Exilarating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>exhilaratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exhilarare</ets> to gladden;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>hilarare</ets> to make merry,
<ets>hilaris</ets> merry, cheerful. See <er>Hilarious</er>.]</ety>
<def>To make merry or jolly; to enliven; to animate; to gladden greatly;
to cheer; <as>as, good news <ex>exhilarates</ex> the mind; wine
<ex>exhilarates</ex> a man.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exhilarate</ent>⟦br⟧

